<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-the-frenet-serret-frame">
  <title>The Frenet-Serret frame</title>

  <objectives>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Describe a curve's local geometry using the unit tangent, unit normal, and binormal.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Relate curvature and torsion to how a curve bends and twists in space.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Decompose acceleration into tangential and normal components using the moving frame.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </objectives>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Introduction goes here.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Unit tangent:
        <me>
          \bv{t}=\frac{\bv{r}'}{\norm{\bv{r}'}}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Unit normal:
        <me>
          \bv{n}=\frac{\bv{t}'}{\norm{\bv{t}'}}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Curvature:
        <me>
          \kappa=\norm{\dv{\bv{t}}{s}}=\frac{\norm{\bv{t}'}}{\norm{\bv{r}'}}=\frac{\bv{r}'\times\bv{r}''}{\norm{\bv{r}'}^{3}}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Tangent component of acceleration:
        <me>
          \bv a_{t}=\bv{a}\cdot\bv{n}
        </me>
        Normal component of acceleration:
        <me>
          \bv a_{n}=\bv{a}\times\bv{n}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        In 3D, we also get the binormal:
        <me>
          \bv B=\bv{t}\times\bv{n}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Torsion:
        <me>
          \dv{\bv{b}}{s}=-\tau\bv{n}
        </me>
        <me>
          \tau=-\dv{\bv{b}}{s}\cdot\bv{n}=-\dfrac{\bv{b}'\cdot\bv{n}}{\norm{\bv{r}'}}=\dfrac{(\bv{r}'\times\bv{r}'')\cdot\bv{r}'''}{\norm{\bv{r}'\times\bv{r}''}^2}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        The unit tangent, unit normal, and binormal together form the Frenet-Serret frame.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
